<DOC><DOCNO> AP890126-0104 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-01-26-89 1228EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Africa-Lawyers     01-26 0126</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Africa-Lawyers,0129</SECOND><HEAD>Lawyers from South Africa, ANC to Hold Conference</HEAD><DATELINE>HARARE, Zimbabwe (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   White lawyers and academics will meetwith black activists to discuss how the law can be used to fightapartheid in South Africa, organizers said Thursday.   About 35 lawyers and academics will come from South Africa for aconference with about a dozen African National Congress leaders fromEurope and Zambia, according to University of Zimbabwe law professorReg Austin. Most of the lawyers and academics are white.   They will meet Jan. 31 to Feb. 4, organizers said.   Under apartheid, South Africa's 5 million whites control thegovernment and economy while 26 million blacks have no vote innational affairs. The ANC is the main guerrilla group fighting thewhite-run government.</TEXT></DOC>